<sec id="id-1dc48348-362c-43e3-83bb-683e530f5a4c" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:tbx="urn:iso:std:iso:30042:ed-1" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"><title><bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="21e8345a-9547-4188-cf64-2eee697d939c" timestamp="1671534637490"?>Clarifying roles and responsibilities<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="21e8345a-9547-4188-cf64-2eee697d939c"?></bold></title><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="892bac92-57a3-4218-a04e-790c7435df14" timestamp="1671534642667"?>The roles and responsibilities of internal and external stakeholders need to be clarified in relation to the GBV grievance mechanism.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="892bac92-57a3-4218-a04e-790c7435df14"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="eb0f8ebf-bff1-4a25-b13c-a91e6056491f" timestamp="1671534642667"?>The primary responsibility of the implementation of a GBV grievance mechanism is with the top management. However, the initiative can also be driven by any or all the stakeholders.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="eb0f8ebf-bff1-4a25-b13c-a91e6056491f"?></p></sec>